[{"id":"VR000181","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents 4 diagrams. Each diagram shows two adjacent uniform magnetic fields of the same magnitude B with a square conducting loop that is half in one field and half in the other field. The magnetic fields are in opposite directions. The direction of the magnetic field on the left is into the page and the direction of the field on the right is out of the page. Figure 1 shows the square moving horizontally to the right at speed v. Figure 2 shows the square moving vertically upward at speed v. Figure 3 shows the square moving horizontally to the left at speed v. Figure 4 shows the square moving vertically downward at speed v.\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR000181.g01.png\" width=\"455\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Each of the figures above shows two adjacent uniform magnetic fields of the same magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> , but the magnetic fields are in opposite in directions. In each figure, a square conducting loop moves perpendicular to the two magnetic fields at speed <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v\"><math alttext=\"v\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. In which figure is the current in the loop counterclockwise?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR000181_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Figure 1</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Figure 2</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Figure 3</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Figure 4</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">None of the loops will have a counterclockwise current.</p>"],"answer":2}]